  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting the Reinforcement of the Congolese Institutions in the Fight Against Illegal Trafficking of Mineral Resources</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As part of the Reform of the Congolese National Police (PNC) and to support the promotion of a responsible minerals trade, this project is aimed at supporting the reinforcement of the PNC in the fight against illegal exploitation of natural resources in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC). The project contributes to an improved security in and around mining sites, specifically in the provinces of North Kivu, South Kivu, Maniema, Katanga (Actual Haut Katanga and Lualaba provinces) and Kasai Occidental (actual Kasai Central &amp; Kasai provinces). The project aims to strengthen the capacity of 374 police officers in the fight against illegal trafficking of mineral resources. A total of 198 among those trained are deployed through six main mining axes in North and South Kivu provinces. The project also provides equipment and infrastructure to the PNC to maintain security for conflict-free minerals in the mining areas in eastern DRC. The project is closely coordinated with other programming that also focuses on conflict-free minerals by reinforcing the Mining Administration in controlling and monitoring trade throughout the supply chain and the Points de Vente (Points of Sale) or Centres de N&#xE9;goces (Trading Counters).</narrative>
  </description>
